crystalline.guide.crystals.title=Crystals

<<< About >>>

crystalline.guide.crystals.about.title=About
crystalline.guide.crystals.about=There are many types of crystals that you can find and create. This section will inform you of them. When you just create one, it is in the mode "Disabled". Press the "Switch Mode" key to change the mode. The default key for it is 'O'.

<<< Administration >>>

crystalline.guide.crystals.administration.title=Administration Crystal
crystalline.guide.crystals.administration=Administration crystals are §overy§r fun to troll players with. They also cause the most insanity in this mod (without addons, excluding the Rift Crystal). If you use it in the mode "Administration", you can hurt a player by roughly 1.5 hearts if you use it while sneaking, at the cost of 25 insanity, 10 potential, and an Extreme Reagent. If you use it without sneaking, it will push a player in the direction you are looking, at the cost of 5 potential, 10 insanity, and an Extreme Reagent.

<<< Cleansing >>>

crystalline.guide.crystals.cleansing.title=Cleansing Crystal
crystalline.guide.crystals.cleansing=Cleansing crystals can be made with any crystal with quartz all around it. When it is in "Cleansing Reagent" mode, you can right-click them to make Cleansing Reagents at the cost of one potential and a Basic Reagent.

<<< Knowledge >>>

crystalline.guide.crystals.knowledge.title=Knowledge Crystal
crystalline.guide.crystals.knowledge=The knowledge crystal can help you monitor your sanity, so you do not become too insane. When it is in "View Insanity" mode, you can right click without sneaking to see a quick overview, or right click while sneaking to see information about the stage of insanity you are currently in.

<<< Life >>>

crystalline.guide.crystals.life.title=Life Crystal
crystalline.guide.crystals.life=Life crystals have a 25 percent chance to be dropped when a player dies. They can be used for regeneration. Life crystals are a crystal with binding, so you can only use a crystal that is bound to you. See Rebinding for more information.

<<< Rift >>>

crystalline.guide.crystals.rift.title=Rift Crystal
crystalline.guide.crystals.rift=The Rift Crystal has two modes: "Obliterate Block" and "Obliterate Entity". These do what their names suggest they do. They launch a projectile where you are looking, like a snowball. It requires a Rift Reagent, and causes permanent insanity if used with a Rift Reagent.

<<< Universe >>>

crystalline.guide.crystals.universe.title=Universe Crystal
crystalline.guide.crystals.universe=The Universe Crystal has three modes: "Obliterate Block" and "Obliterate Entity", and "Ultra Cleanse". These "Obliterate" modes do what their names suggest they do. They launch a projectile where you are looking, like a snowball. The "Ultra Cleanse" mode clears you of all insanity, but adds 1 insanity, but it can help a lot in clearing permanent insanity. It requires a Universe Reagent, and does not cause any insanity.

